---
import ApiPageHeader from "../components/ApiPageHeader.astro";
import { WORKER_TOOLS } from "../model.ts";

const toolLines = WORKER_TOOLS.map((tool) => `- \`${tool}\``).join("\n");
const markdown = [
  "# For Agentic Editors",
  "",
  "Integrate at host `/v1`, the same local runtime host Studio uses. Your client talks to the host;",
  "models never see `/v1`.",
  "",
  "Start with the Overview quickstart: `GET /v1/source-sessions` → plan → start → poll events. Branch on",
  "receipts and fail-closed envelopes, not on guessed capability.",
  "",
  "## Child worker tools (not host HTTP)",
  "",
  "The names below are grant-scoped tools on ephemeral loopback MCP bridges for child workers.",
  "They are not `/v1` routes. Do not call them as REST endpoints.",
  "",
  toolLines,
  "",
].join("\n");
---

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-agents-heading">
  <ApiPageHeader
    title="For Agentic Editors"
    headingId="api-agents-heading"
    description="Integrate at /v1 on the local host. Worker tool names are child MCP grants, not REST routes."
    markdown={markdown}
  />
  <p>
    Use <code>/v1</code> when your editor needs to branch on proof: which ranges are speech, in
    which language, where speakers overlap, which lines are evidence-backed or withheld, and what
    one exact span means. Each of those returns as a receipt with lineage.
  </p>
  <p>
    Your client talks to the host. The models doing the work never see <code>/v1</code>. Follow
    the <a href="/api/">Overview</a> core flow and quickstart before captions or language
    explanations.
  </p>
  <h2 id="api-agents-tools-heading">Child Worker Tools</h2>
  <p>
    Grant-scoped tools over ephemeral loopback bridges. Workers cannot grant themselves
    capability, choose their own path, or widen their scope. These names are not host HTTP routes.
  </p>
  <ul class="api-tools" aria-label="Grant-scoped worker tools (not /v1 routes)">
    {WORKER_TOOLS.map((tool) => (
      <li>{tool}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
</section>
